25/08/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- US Ambassador to Greece Thomas Miller visited some of the facilities that will be used next summer when Athens hosts the 2004 Olympics. During Friday's (22 August) visit, he said Greece and the United States are working very closely on security, adding that co-operation must continue. He rejected a recent <I>New York Times </I> article suggesting an al Qaeda presence in Greece. He also denied a report that Australia was insisting on protecting its own athletes during the Games, amid concerns that Greece could not handle security. (MPA - 22/08/03)
